THE Broadcasting Complaints Commission (BCCSA) 
says 702 radio presenter Eusebius McKaiser created a hostile 
environment and demonstrated intolerance during a discussion 
program in May.The BCCSA has reprimanded 702 for contravening clause 13 of the Broadcasting Code.Clause
 13 states that a broadcaster must make 
reasonable efforts to fairly present opposing points of view, on 
